display.shortDescription: A lower temperature profile targeted at darker roasts.
display.description: This is a flow profile in the same style as the similarly named default profile on Decent machines. It was intended to target good espresso for sipping from dark beans by trying to maximize flavors for those that don't like dark roasts, and minimize the extraction of things that some people consider 'bad' in dark roasts.  It intentionally has a lower extraction for those reasons.  Suggestion is to pull as a 1:1 shot, but works up to 2:1. If pulling as a 2:1 ratio, consider a small up-dose and courser grind to get target flow rate.  Flow rates in extraction should be 0.5-1.2ml/s; the darker the roast, the lower the flow.
